  "report": {
    "narrative": [
      "Across the 2026-03-01..2026-03-24 historical window, the strongest health signals available in the preview point to (1) scheduler/capacity pressure at the partition level and (2) a small set of thermal GPU hotspots at the host level. Evidence for other major risk classes (fabric/InfiniBand health, storage SMART degradation, and explicit node/Slurm state anomalies like DOWN/DRAIN) is not present in the preview, so confidence is limited outside of scheduler pressure and GPU temperature.\n\nHighest-risk hosts (host-level evidence): the clearest host-specific risk comes from ROCm-reported GPU temperatures. The top hotspot is k002-004-v5 (GPU card 0) peaking at 82°C, followed closely by k002-004-v7 at 81°C and k002-004-v1 at 79°C. Multiple k002-004-* nodes appear in the top list, which can indicate a rack/row airflow or shared workload pattern (or simply that these nodes were the busiest), but workload/utilization context is not included in this preview.\n\nDominant risk categories:\n- Scheduler/capacity pressure (strong, but not host-specific): pending jobs are concentrated in mi3001x (36) and mi2104x (26). Several partitions show CPU saturation at or near 1.0 (mi3008x, mi3258x, mi3508x), consistent with broad contention.\n- Thermal hotspots (moderate-to-strong host-specific evidence): a handful of GPUs are running in the high 70s to low 80s °C.\n- Hardware, fabric, storage (weak evidence): no SMART metrics, no InfiniBand counters/errors, and no explicit GPU fault/error counters are shown, so hardware/fabric/storage risk cannot be ranked reliably from this preview.\n\nEvidence strength caveats:\n- Strong: partition pending counts and saturation values (directly reported).\n- Moderate: GPU temperatures (directly reported, but missing accompanying utilization/power/fan speed and duration-at-temp).\n- Weak/absent: node health states, SMART, InfiniBand health, GPU fault signals (not present in preview), so the fleet-wide “operational risk” ranking is necessarily incomplete."
    ],
    "highlights": [
      "Top host-level risk signal available: GPU thermal hotspots on k002-004-v5 (82°C), k002-004-v7 (81°C), k002-004-v1 (79°C).",
      "Cluster-level operational risk is dominated by scheduler pressure: highest pending demand in partitions mi3001x (36) and mi2104x (26).",
      "Several partitions are at full CPU saturation (value=1.0): mi3008x, mi3258x, mi3508x, suggesting broad contention rather than an isolated queue.",
      "Evidence gap: no InfiniBand error/health counters, no storage SMART indicators, and no node state (DOWN/DRAIN) signals shown—hardware/fabric/storage risk ranking is low-confidence from this preview."
    ],
